President Trump addressed members of Congress and their families at the annual White House Congressional Picnic. He expressed his gratitude for their service and highlighted the accomplishments of his administration, including job creation, tax cuts, criminal justice reform, and efforts to combat the opioid crisis. He also mentioned the passage of VA Choice and VA Accountability, which have improved healthcare for veterans. The President emphasized that these achievements are not just political victories, but national victories for the country. He thanked the members of Congress for their work and urged them to enjoy the event and put politics aside.